# Views and Routing Guide

The application follows a view-based architecture with Vue Router for navigation.

## View Structure

1. [Home.vue](mdc:src/views/Home.vue)
   - Landing page
   - Project introduction
   - Start game button
   - Feature overview

2. [Generate.vue](mdc:src/views/Generate.vue)
   - Ancestor generation interface
   - Surname input/random generation
   - Ancestor card preview
   - Typing effect for quotes

3. [Interaction.vue](mdc:src/views/Interaction.vue)
   - Main interaction interface
   - Offering buttons (incense, flowers, kowtow)
   - Emotion display
   - Evolution progress
   - Quote display with typing effect

4. [Quotes.vue](mdc:src/views/Quotes.vue)
   - Today's quotes list
   - Favorites management
   - Quote sharing
   - Quote card generation

5. [MiniGames.vue](mdc:src/views/MiniGames.vue)
   - Game selection interface
   - Translation quiz game
   - Red packet reward game
   - Score tracking

6. [Share.vue](mdc:src/views/Share.vue)
   - Share template selection
   - Preview generation
   - Social media sharing
   - Image/link generation

## Routing System

The router configuration in [router/index.js](mdc:src/router/index.js) includes:

1. Route Guards
   - Authentication check
   - Ancestor existence check
   - State loading

2. Meta Information
   - Page titles
   - Required states
   - Transition names

3. Navigation
   - History mode enabled
   - Lazy loading for views
   - Scroll behavior management

4. Error Handling
   - 404 fallback
   - Invalid state redirects
   - Loading states
